    <div class="democontainer">
    <p class="sectionheader">Deconstructed Triangle</p>
    <span class="demobox"></span>
    <span class="demobox-explanation">
    <ol>
      <li>Take a box...with equally sized borders</li>
      <li>...and shrink it to 0 height and width...</li>
      <li>To create a triangle, focus on the border opposite from the triangle's main vertex (the direction you want the triangle to be pointing)...and set attributes you want (color, size, etc.)</li>
      <li>The larger the border size, the larger the triangle</li>
      <li>Make the adjacent borders transparent</li>
    </ol>
  </span>
  </div>

